title: $92M rehab planned for affordable apartments

Home / News / Construction & Development / $92M rehab planned for affordable apartments The Seward Towers, at 2910 E. Franklin Ave, will be rehabbed over 18 months starting next spring. (Staff photo: Bill Klotz) $92M rehab planned for affordable apartments By: Cali Owings July 28, 2015 7:04 am 0 After two years of planning, the financing for the 640-unit affordable housing preservation project is nearing completion.
